*pacman* *basics*
-S <package>            *install*
-R <package>            *remove*
-Rs <package>           *remove* package and its unique dependencies
-Q                      *list* installed packages
-Qs <string1> <string2> *search* installed packages (supports regular expressions)
-Qi <package>           diplay more information about a package
-Ss <string1> <string2> *search* sync database packages
-Si <package>           diplay more information about a package
-Qe                     list explicitly installed packages
-Qn <group>             list packages in a group
-Qm                     list foreign packages (not installed from the official repositories)
-Syu                    *update* all packages and synchronizes the repository databases
-Qdt                    list packages no longer required as dependencies
-Qet                    list packages explicitely installed and no longer required as dependencies
Never run pacman -Sy always run -Syu instead
When getting issues installing try updating the system first
Use yay -Syu to also update the AUR packages
